      "content": "but you're kind of dodging the main point. if we look at the actual economic logic, you can't have less incentive to work and call it a \"societal contribution\" just to balance a sentence. isn't it more accurate to say that these programs create a structural dependency that actively hurts the labor market by keeping people from participating in productive work?",
